Here is a handout that goes through the algebra of a planning problem in Shimer&rsquo;s manuscript, Labor Markets and Business Cycles. The setup of the problem is non-standard and unlike the problems we&rsquo;ve solved all year, although this point is subtle. After laying out the problem, the non-standard approach is taken to first solve the problem following the lecture notes. Second, the problem is solved following the algorithm we&rsquo;ve used all year; namely, writing the problem so that we choose next period&rsquo;s state. Of course the two approaches yield the same solution.
The handout is available here.
